					</div>
					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Claire Thompson</h4>
												<p>Claire Thompson is a former longtime seasonal trail worker for the U.S. Forest Service, a teacher at Wenatchee Valley college, and an MFA student in Nature Writing at Western Colorado University. Her work is published or forthcoming in Qu, High Country News, Parabola, Out There Outdoors, Camas, The Thalweg, and Terrain.org, among others. She is working on a book about the impacts of climate, political, and economic change on public-lands stewardship. Claire calls the mountains of North Central Washington home.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			
